      "body" : "can you be more specific about &lt;jarfile&gt; argument? If my error is <code>bad class file: &#47;usr&#47;share&#47;openjfx&#47;lib&#47;javafx.graphics.jar!&#47;javafx&#47;applicati&zwnj;&#8203;on&#47;Platform.class     class file has wrong version 54.0, should be 52.0     Please remove or make sure it appears in the correct subdirectory of the classpath.</code> then is the jarfile <code>graphics.jar</code>?"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 13615054,
      "reputation" : 839,
      "user_id" : 9821205,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Ry_ehPbcnJ0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAGI/2-jHFQt7cjk/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "BUGATTI  AJAY",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/9821205/bugatti-ajay"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : -1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1700000879,
    "last_edit_date" : 1700000879,
    "creation_date" : 1626932533,
    "answer_id" : 68479720,
    "question_id" : 28180915,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If the issue is in IntelliJ, then do this in the terminal (not in the IntelliJ terminal):</p>\n<ol>\n<li>change the Java version to an appropriate one (in my case, using JDK 1.4 as the issue was <code>class file has wrong version 55.0, should be 52.0</code>)</li>\n<li><code>java -Dspring.profiles.active=test -jar build/libs/&lt;jarname&gt;.jar</code> <br />\nRun this</li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 10794010,
      "reputation" : 1812,
      "user_id" : 7940437,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Fm8yr.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Majid Roustaei",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7940437/majid-roustaei"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 9,
    "last_activity_date" : 1700002136,
    "last_edit_date" : 1700002136,
    "creation_date" : 1641373812,
    "answer_id" : 70590286,
    "question_id" : 28180915,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Generally this kind of error happens when you try run a <code>.class</code> file which is compiled with another version of Java.</p>\n<p>In your case, it is compiled with <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_version_history#Java_SE_8\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Java 8</a> (major version -&gt; 52) and you want to run it with <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_version_history#Java_SE_6\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Java 6</a> (major version -&gt; 50).</p>\n<p>Here is a list of major versions of Java and SE version:\n<a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jvms/se17/html/jvms-4.html#jvms-4.1-200-B.2\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Class file format major versions</a></p>\n<p>To solve the problem, use the same version of the compiled class file, based on your project structure.\nIn IntelliJ IDEA: Menu <em>File</em> → <em>Project Structure</em> → <em>Project</em> → <em>Project SDK</em></p>\n<p>In case of using builder tools like <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apache_Maven\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Maven</a>, this configuration also should be changed in the corresponding settings. Here is an example of how it is done in a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apache_Maven#Project_Object_Model\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">POM</a> file:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;properties&gt;\n    &lt;java.version&gt;11&lt;/java.version&gt;\n    &lt;maven.compiler.source&gt;${java.version}&lt;/maven.compiler.source&gt;\n    &lt;maven.compiler.target&gt;${java.version}&lt;/maven.compiler.target&gt;\n&lt;/properties&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 9983336,
        "reputation" : 5256,
        "user_id" : 7769052,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 75,
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/t94zs.jpg?s=256",
        "display_name" : "camilajenny",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7769052/camilajenny"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1643632516,
      "post_id" : 70872597,
      "comment_id" : 125383694,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "the versions you mentioned are wrong. It should be 8 (52.0) and 6 (50.0) instead of 11 (55.0) and 8."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 14248629,
      "reputation" : 291,
      "user_id" : 10292838,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/tARRE.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "N.Neupane",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/10292838/n-neupane"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1700002236,
    "last_edit_date" : 1700002236,
    "creation_date" : 1643250445,
    "answer_id" : 70872597,
    "question_id" : 28180915,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>The error signifies that you may have the dependencies that are compiled in Java 11, but you are using Java 8, so there are two options left. You can either migrate to Java 11 or ask the library developer to provide you with a Java 8 build.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 16863493,
      "reputation" : 57,
      "user_id" : 16555594,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-AHy24rWhEZ0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/ACHi3rc_EhfcPL01GKGY-Kz4AWtT4dt2Uw/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Ritik Raj",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/16555594/ritik-raj"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1700002305,
    "last_edit_date" : 1700002305,
    "creation_date" : 1665984103,
    "answer_id" : 74092858,
    "question_id" : 28180915,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Class version 52 is <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_version_history#Java_SE_8\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Java 8</a>. You need Java 11.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6676840,
      "reputation" : 3461,
      "user_id" : 5151202,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/kTtrB.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "times29",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5151202/times29"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1700002327,
    "last_edit_date" : 1700002327,
    "creation_date" : 1667812934,
    "answer_id" : 74344300,
    "question_id" : 28180915,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I installed a new JDK version, but I forgot to set the <code>JAVA_HOME</code> environment variable to the new JDK. Setting it to the correct version helped!</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 12858978,
      "reputation" : 431,
      "user_id" : 9301392,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/06cf63fe26887e2ed39fbb1f6fcf4e32?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "AnushaSP07",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/9301392/anushasp07"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 28,
    "last_activity_date" : 1700002856,
    "last_edit_date" : 1700002856,
    "creation_date" : 1674493226,
    "answer_id" : 75212710,
    "question_id" : 28180915,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Check the version of Java it is showing in the error:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>45 = Java 1.1</li>\n<li>46 = Java 1.2</li>\n<li>47 = Java 1.3</li>\n<li>48 = Java 1.4</li>\n<li>49 = Java 5</li>\n<li>50 = Java 6</li>\n<li>51 = Java 7</li>\n<li>52 = Java 8</li>\n<li>53 = Java 9</li>\n<li>54 = Java 10</li>\n<li>55 = Java 11</li>\n<li>56 = Java 12</li>\n<li>57 = Java 13</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Install/download that JDK in program files/Java folder.</p>\n<p>In Eclipse or STS, right click on project → <em>Build Path</em> → <em>Libraries</em> → add JRE system libraries → add the version of JDK showing in the error as an alternate JRE.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/oS5jQ.jpg\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/oS5jQ.jpg\" alt=\"Enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6017591,
      "reputation" : 41,
      "user_id" : 4725838,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/39c6e314167a5968c2d40b5f43b9e420?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Ajay Kumar Sinha",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4725838/ajay-kumar-sinha"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : -1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1700002638,
    "last_edit_date" : 1700002638,
    "creation_date" : 1676457436,
    "answer_id" : 75458521,
    "question_id" : 28180915,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I have solved this by changing my <a href=\"https://maven.apache.org/pom.html#What_is_the_POM.3F\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">pom.xml</a> file:</p>\n<pre><code>&lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;\n&lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-parent&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n&lt;version&gt;2.6.4&lt;/version&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Change 3.0.2 to 2.6.4.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 8617529,
      "reputation" : 121,
      "user_id" : 6453791,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 40,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/OM2x7.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "N. I. Md. Ashafuddula",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6453791/n-i-md-ashafuddula"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1700002915,
    "last_edit_date" : 1700002915,
    "creation_date" : 1677559497,
    "answer_id" : 75587959,
    "question_id" : 28180915,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I am using <strong>JDK 1.8.0_131</strong> and For my case, the version code <code>&lt;version&gt;2.7.5&lt;/version&gt;</code> in <strong>pom.xml</strong> and <code>module -&gt; language level 8</code> solved my issue.</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>    &lt;parent&gt;\n        &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;\n        &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-parent&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n        &lt;version&gt;2.7.5&lt;/version&gt;\n        &lt;relativePath/&gt;\n    &lt;/parent&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1688556,
      "reputation" : 1012,
      "user_id" : 1551368,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/6f56b22655fa63b7f8124a1d2c253ca3?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "dobrivoje",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1551368/dobrivoje"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1677869182,
    "creation_date" : 1677869182,
    "answer_id" : 75630803,
    "question_id" : 28180915,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I couldn't change an SDK version, so I had to lower maven dependency of the library causing this error.\nI've had SDK 1.8_191, and I had to use TestNG 6.14.3, as versions 7.x wouldn't work.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3638345,
      "reputation" : 949,
      "user_id" : 3033184,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/nzy3e.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Gus",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3033184/gus"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1700003006,
    "last_edit_date" : 1700003006,
    "creation_date" : 1682405610,
    "answer_id" : 76098339,
    "question_id" : 28180915,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Project's <a href=\"https://docs.gradle.org/current/userguide/tutorial_using_tasks.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">build.gradle</a> file:</p>\n<pre><code>allprojects {    tasks.withType(org.jetbrains.kotlin.gradle.tasks.AbstractKotlinCompile).configureEach {\n        kotlinOptions {\n            jvmTarget = &quot;1.8&quot;\n            apiVersion = &quot;1.8&quot;\n            languageVersion = &quot;1.8&quot;\n        }\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 13065194,
        "reputation" : 103,
        "user_id" : 9440826,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/f4vgu.jpg?s=256",
